The SureFire high-capacity magazine for 5.56x45 mm (.223 Remington) ammunition, is compatible with M4/M16/AR-15 variants and other firearms that accept standard STANAG 4179 magazines. Constructed from Mil-Spec hard-anodized aluminum, they feed smoothly and reliably due to optimal geometry, non-binding coil springs, and ingenious nesting polymer followers. SureFire High-Capacity magazines provide distinct tactical advantages: increased initial firepower in ambush situations; fewer reloads overall, which means less downtime and target distraction in a firefight; fast and easy magazine insertion, even with a closed bolt; less bulk compared to drum mags, enabling a normal weapon grip. The 60-round magazine—slightly thinner than two 30-round magazines clipped together and about the same overall length—fits in most dual magazine pouches, eliminating special carry pouches required for drum magazines.

title: For Sale/Trade:  RE: scammer Berry Moss. Simply untrue.
postcontent:
First off, I am sorry to disrupt your shopping with this petty argument. 

This is in fact, Berry Moss.  I am thankful that we live in a country where a man has an opportunity to defend his reputation.

The "scam alert" ad comes from a man who offered me 15% less than retail on my bersa 380, and my bodyguard 380.  Sounds reasonable, right? He then quoted $300 for the bersa as retail, and $330 for the bodyguard.

So, let's take a look at the figures. 300 minus 15% is $255. 330 minus 15% is $280.50. 
I declined his off respectfully(which I am entitled to do). He wrote a few anti-Semitic comments(and while I am not Jewish, it is still not very good business practice). I admittedly responded harshly, rather than turning the other cheek.

Might I ad that my advertisement reads, "For Trade".  

The intention of this ad is to defend my reputation, not to put down the person who insulted me.  He shall remain nameless, simply because I respect others' privacy enough not to place their names in a public forum.

Should there be any persons out there who were considering doing business with me, and were swayed by his advertisement, I will gladly forward you the transcript of our email conversation leading to this slanderous post regarding my business ethics. I will also provide references for persons I have done business with in the past if you care to speak with them(after receiving their approval to do so, of course).

Thanks for reading.

Best Regards,
Berry Moss
